# Design Information Modelling (Part 6) - Walkthrough

## 1. Architecture & Library Refactoring (Phase 6.1)
The data layer has been cleaned up and consolidated:
- Migrated the central `store.ts` to [src/lib/zustand.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/lib/zustand.ts).
- Renamed the legacy dictionary hook to [useDesignDictionaries](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/components/layout/design/DesignDictionaries.ts#15-73).
- Eradicated obsolete UI files: `DesignPart.tsx`, `DesignDesign.tsx`, `DesignCreationWizard.tsx`, `DesignCatalogSidebar.tsx`, and `DesignAssembly.tsx`.
- Renamed `AssemblyTimeline.tsx` to [DesignTimeline.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/components/layout/design/DesignTimeline.tsx).

## 2. DesignTools & DesignAdd Refactoring (Phase 6.2)
The authoring interface now reflects the true PDM architecture:
- [DesignTools](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/components/layout/design/DesignTools.tsx#30-402) constants in the backend have been updated to export the core entities: **Sketch, Part, Assembly, Bundle, and Design**.
- A central `<DesignAdd />` wrapper component has been built to replace the old Sidebar.
- Scaffolded 5 distinct sub-interfaces for inserting elements: `DesignSketchAdd`, `DesignPartAdd`, `DesignAssemblyAdd`, `DesignBundleAdd`, `DesignDesignMerge`.
- The [DesignTools.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/components/layout/design/DesignTools.tsx) HUD toolbar dynamically loops through the backend `PDMTools` constant to render the insertion buttons perfectly matching the schema.

## 3. Advanced DesignTerminal CLI v2 (Phase 6.3)
The terminal has been fundamentally rewritten with a robust AST (Abstract Syntax Tree) parsing engine.
- **Entity Selection** (`@`): Typing `@` brings up a live search dropdown querying the local `entities` store. Mouse clicks on the 3D scene also auto-populate `@id` in the prompt.
- **Tool Mapping** (`#`): Typing `#` suggests tools (`#move`, `#add`, `#delete`, etc) matching the new PDM constants.
- **Axis Operations** (`/`): Implemented parametric support for modifying vectors directly (e.g. `/x+1`, `/y-1.5`, `/z20`).
- **Interactive Numeric Scrubbing**: With the cursor hovering over a numeric parameter in the CLI, pressing the **Arrow Up / Arrow Down** keys will continuously scrub the 3D value by `0.001` increments (or `1.0` if holding `Shift`).
- **Keyboard Navigation**: Implemented full `Up/Down` arrow and `Enter/Tab` selection for the Autocomplete popover.

## 4. WebXR Interactivity & Spatial UI (Phase 6.4)
- **Grab & Move**: Reimplemented object interaction using strict pointer event captures (`onPointerDown`/`onPointerUp`/`onPointerMove`) combined with `setPointerCapture`, natively supported by Fiber & WebXR. This wraps both the generic nodes ([GenericPart](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/components/layout/design/GenericPart.tsx#13-542)) and instance layers ([InstancedPartGroup](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/components/layout/design/InstancedPartGroup.tsx#12-164)).
- **Spatial UI (3D Dashboard)**: Built a reactive 3D widget ([SpatialUI.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/components/layout/design/SpatialUI.tsx)) anchored to the camera view (`<XRSpace space="viewer">`) allowing the user to select menus, translate models, open parts, and dismiss selections without taking off the VR headset. 
- Fixed [DesignTools.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/components/layout/design/DesignTools.tsx) compilation errors dealing with WebXR component types.

## 5. PDM Data Model & Cloud Rendering (Phase 6.5)
- **Textures**: Added the `compatibleMaterials` property and updated field permissions (Policy Matrix).
- **Parts**: Added the `defaultTextureId` field configuration allowing better mapping from 2D planning straight to 3D representation.
- **Admin Portal UI**: 
  - Integrated a multi-selector in `/admin/pdm/textures` for managing compatible Materials.
  - Implemented the "Advanced Photorealism" tab in `/admin/pdm/materials` handling `clearcoat`, `sheen`, `transmission`, and `ior` sliders for advanced visualization.
- **LOD Generation**: Added a new Firebase Cloud Function (`choreographyMeshGenerateLOD`) responding to mesh uploads inside Google Cloud Storage.

## Validation
- The `npm run build` process succeeds cleanly with `0` errors, confirming correct refactoring of Zustand imports and removal of legacy dependencies.
