- The `npx tsc --noEmit` checks passed successfully, confirming correct Typescript alignments for XR and PDM features.

## 6. Workspace UI & Tools Expansion (Part 6)
- **DesignTools Constants**: Upgraded [functions/src/core/constants.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/functions/src/core/constants.ts) with explicit `order` indexing and `guest` boolean flags, categorizing actions cleanly into [add](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/lib/design.ts#10-35), `edit`, `mrp`, `view`, `share`, and `general` groups.
- **UI Architecture**: Solidified the [DesignTools](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/components/layout/design/DesignTools.tsx#30-402) widget using fixed absolute positioning (128x16) and a flexible, interactive inner `.ui-design-tools-wrapper`.
- **Component Refactoring**: Deeply refactored [DesignTools.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/components/layout/design/DesignTools.tsx):
  - Dynamically mapping tools via `Object.values(PDMTools)` to ensure a perfect 1:1 parity between Backend configurations and Frontend toolbars.
  - Extracted business logic (Duplicate, Delete operations) out into a modular API (`DesignController` inside [src/lib/design.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/lib/design.ts)).
  - Added smart conditional visibility context (Tools in the `edit` group only appear when an entity is actively selected).
  - Wired up the `ACCOUNT` tool to directly log out authenticated users or direct guests to the authentication portal.

## 7. Unified CLI & Tool Syntax (Part 7)
- **Terminal Parsing**: Refactored the AST core engine of [DesignTerminal.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/components/layout/design/DesignTerminal.tsx) to directly interpret `#` (Edit group) and `&` (Add group) against the backend entity map `PDMTools`.
- **Dispatcher Consolidation**: Deprecated the massive internal `switch` statement of [DesignTools.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/components/layout/design/DesignTools.tsx) to favor the universal `DesignController.executeToolCommand(toolId)`. This ensures hitting a tool via UI or triggering it via CLI Command fires the exact same functional sequence organically.
- **Help Documentation**: Rewrote `/help` syntax to `--help` and bound it natively to the `PDMTools` configuration matrix, exposing live help documentation built straight from the backend constants.
